-- American Express quarterly profit rises 8 pct
-- By Avik Das in Bangalore
-- Wed Oct 15, 2014 04:14PM EDT
-- None



Oct 15 (Reuters) - American Express Co <AXP.N>, the world's largest credit card issuer, reported an 8.1 percent rise in quarterly profit as customers spent more using the company's credit cards.

Net income rose to $1.48 billion, or $1.40 per share, in the third quarter ended Sept. 30 from $1.37 billion, or $1.25 per share, a year earlier. [ID:nBw6d6YQGa]